rComments: Go to her office hours and 100% you will get an A+. She is amazing. Don't hesitate to ask her about your papers.

Took her asynchronous class, one word : AWFUL. You have zero contact with the teacher, which is unfortunate, it's hard to know what she's expecting from you. She posts PowerPoints and a voice recording of her reading word for word the PowerPoints, useless and lacks explanation overall. Lots of work to do that are worth little percentages.

It is not really about the teacher but about the asynchronous classes: IT WAS BAD! Never having a real contact with a teacher is not very appreciated by all. Other than that, there's a lot of works to do in this class but it is manageable in the end.

This class was asynchronism so I can't say a lot for the teacher but she seems nice. There is a lot to cover in this class but it's pretty basic things. If you're comfortable with the language then you won't have any problems. Lots of reading.

She was like a ghost, you only interacted with TAs. Most assignments were pointless and redundant. There were so many but all worth little percentages. Expectations weren't always clear whilst grading and communication was poor. Gready to read 2 books, but they're not long. The class wasn't hard but I didn't learn much. Final exam was a take home.
It's asynchronous but prof Ghadie is the best. If you took French class in Quebec, you're good :)) Amazing prof with clear grading. Love her! The grammar textbook is not necessary.
A very nice and organized online class. It was asynchronous and everything was easy to follow without confusion. Good professor and seems like a very nice person.
The books were some of the best French books I have ever read. You could do the class whenever you wanted because there was no live calls.
Madame Heba est une tres bonne professeure. Faites le travail chaque semaine et vous aurez une bonne note. Elle est disponible aussi pour répondre aux questions, elle ma bcp aider.

Study, and youll do great. Its as simple as that. I really like her, I had her in my first year for a grammar class and now am taking this one with her. If I was confused she was always there to help, you just need to ask. You can tell she tries really hard to make the class as clear as possible. Literally just do your work and ask questions.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I've only been taking this class online so my rating might be biased as I'm sure it would be a different experience in person, but this class is not very well adapted to online learning at all. The lectures are basically poor quality audio recordings that you listen to in the background as you read power point slides.

Basically your final grade will depend on the TA mood. The professor doesn't care about you even if you try to communicate with her she will dont care about what you are saying. Even if you don't understand she will tell you to hear her audio class. Very boring and very hard. We had to complete huges assignments every week to get 1% for each.
An ok class. Very overwhelming and unclear at times. So many tasks that were only worth 1%, yet required hours of work for quality. Lectures were long and hard to complete. (because they were boring)

I'm completing my fourth year in French lit and there is absolutely no reason for me to do this bad in a fourth year class. This is the class I put the most effort into with the worst outcome. Prepare to literally write down every single word she says if you want to at least get a 50 in this class. She gives barely any feedback don't take this prof

The TAs correct all the work so the grading really depends on what TA you get. Other than that theres 2 grammar quizzes and 2 quizzes on the books, the questions for the quizzes on the books can get pretty specific but its not to bad.

Ultimately your assigned TA will determine your final grade. Mine was awfully strict. What's more, they ask us to complete lengthy weekly portfolios worth 1% each but make us write a critique in there the same length as the actual exams worth 20%. Where's the logic? You'll struggle to write a text under 400 words as asked. Reading exams are tricky.

I'm sure professor Ghadie is a great prof in person and the structure of the online class was definitely not her fault but can someone tell me why in my 3 years of STEM classes, FRA1710 was the most difficult? Do yourself a favour and wait to take it in person. The weekly assignments aren't worth it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Easy class. Great TA. Prof doesn't give too much homework and if you work hard you'll get a good grade in the class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Her lectures are very boring. It is easy to distract yourself but as long as you do the work, lectures aren't really mandatory. The tests on the book lectures are extremely specific and grammar tests have multiple trick questions. However, the essay gets graded by the TA's so it depends on the TA you get for those grades.
Average prof, I feel like I didn't learn much in this class.. classes could literally only last 20 minutes and she would let us go... Just feels like she wants to end her lessons quickly!
Overall a good prof. The actual lectures were very boring but she was always very positive and straightforward with what she expected from her students.

Easiest course I have taken so far. The course content is easy and she posts all her lectures online. You can tell that she cares about the students however, I have never needed to contact her outside class.

She is very nice and calming. The lectures were dreadful, it wasnt exciting, and I wish she wouldve done more to lighten up the 8:30 am class. You dont really have to attend the lectures, as long as you review the material online.
Really disappointed as to having a hard time understanding her with her accent. I thought for sure my french teacher would be one I could understand easily but unfortunately its not the case.

She is the best prof i have ever had in university. I had her three times and she is genuinely caring and wants to see her students do well and pass. She's truly amazing and she puts all of the notes online.

Cette prof est vraiment fantastique. Elle tient à coeur la réussite de ses étudiants. C'est ma première fois d'avoir un cours avec elle et ça me rend un peu triste que j'en aurai pas d'autres. Elle encourage les rencontres pour discuter des projets et des examens. Elle veut qu'il n'y ait aucunes ambiguités donc elle s'explique normalement très bien

One of the best prof I've had at Uni. Super caring, very smart, always in a good mood, perfect speech paste and tone, very easy to understand, funny and genuine. She has a great energy. Makes the class enjoyable.

J'ai beaucoup aimé ce prof. Elle avait toujours un sourire sur le visage, même à 8:30. Quant aux examen, elle est compréhensive des nuances. Elle augmentera ta note si la justification est bonne! Pour moi, +13% examen final parce que je me suis débattu. Elle expliquera tout en cas d'incertitude. Très bon prof d'après moi. Cours FRA25020 facile
Very little insight or feedback given by this teacher and she moves too quicly with her schedule leaving those that haven't mastered the content of previous classes, behind.

You really need to know the material before doing the tests because you can't wing them. As long as you practice your verb and look over your the grammar rules you should be good. She really cares about her students and really wants us to learn. She was great!!

Super nice prof, she wants you to succeed. French grammar is an easy class if you did lots of grammar in high school, but not easy at all if you're a native english speaker. You basically learn everything in 4months. Her tests however are fair and she gives bonus points. The final was easier than the tests.
Qu'est-ce tu veux que je dise, c'est un cours de grammaire .. si le français c'est ta langue maternelle, sa va aller par contre si tu es anglophone, bonne chance !
Son cours est très facile. Je le reprendrais avec plaisir, mais peut-être sans elle. Malgré sa gentillesse et sa patience, elle a enseigné quelque chose de mauvais et ça m'a refroidi.
Il faut lire les livres du cours. Le prof est juste.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Le cours est vraiment facile. S'il s'avère difficile, Heba va tout faire pour nous expliquer clairement la matière. Ça ne lui dérange pas de répéter quarante fois s'il le faut, la réussite de ses étudiants lui tient à coeur. Elle est tellement fine et prend la peine de nous parler quand vient le temps des exercices. Je vous la conseille x100!!!!!!
love her, best French prof ever! she is soooo sweet omg!

She is a very sweet person and cares a lot about the success of her students. She is also very clear and detailed in the way she teaches. However, her lectures are long and boring. This class was pretty easy, you could easily pass it by only reading the novels and not show up to any lectures.

She really cares about her students. Her lectures are however very long and she often goes on tangents about random non pertinent things. The class size dindled through the semester so she ended up given those who attended the lectures extra hints for the essay and exam.
Tres bonne prof, elle est tres claire sur la matiere ainsi que ses attentes. Si vous ecoutez en classe, vous n'aurez aucun probleme a avoir une bonne note.

shes a good prof but DONT TAKE FRA2520!  it seems simple on the sylabus but it was the hardest class i took.  lots of rules to learn and memorize and the test seem simple but are hard because of the different rules. i regret taking this class.
Prof. Ghadie is amazing! The LECs are a bit long but for the papers, she gives answers in class. DGDs are a must. Her TA's were really nice.

The course content was bland, lectures were long, and one of the assigned novels, Thérèse Raquin, was horrible, but Prof Ghadie is really sweet and will help you with the writing assignments. Tests were quite easy and the two texts didn't take long to write. The magistraux aren't that essential though, but attend the DGD.

Took a second year french grammar class with her as an elective. I have received 80+ in every french class I've taken, including two french classes in first year but failed this class. Heba is the nicest lady but she doesn't teach the rules and application of grammar well at all. Don't take this class!!
Les cours magistraux sont complètement inutile selon moi... J'ai pas rien appris, pis ouin.

Best prof this semester! Extremely clear with what she expects of students. She posts all her PowerPoints on Blackboard, so I quickly realised going to class when there was no evaluation was a waste of time. We had a 'résumé' and a 'compte rendu' to redact, and she gave good examples of both texts. Follow the models and you should get 15/15!

Professor Ghadie is very passionate about her subject and she's very helpful. If you don't understand something, go see her! She's super sweet and will answer you questions. She's very clear about her expectations. I suggest going to the lectures because she gives answers in class. DGDs are mandatory! She's an amazing prof to have.

Shows that she's very passionate about it. Very helpful and improve your french. She's very clear in everything (assignments as well) If you listen and practice a bit you should be good cause they're a lot of grammar exercise.. She's very nice too. ATTENDANCE MANDATORY FOR THE DGD

Dr. Heba is absolutely lovely, really. She's really passionate in her lectures and she's clear in what she expects from us students. If you really don't get something, just go up to her and she will happily explain it to you. In fact, you should go see her in her office because she really guides you to get the best grade possible. :) love her

Heba is passionate about what she teaches and sets clear guidelines for the work that she assigns. She was also there for me when I had concerns and made sure that I, as well as the other students, understood the material. Best professor of my freshman year for sure!
Lectures are incredibly long, but i've personally never had a pleasant french class. She is a great prof, the books we had to read were a piece of cake. I would recommend her to everyone.
One of the best French teachers. Clear and her lectures are long but useful (sometimes)
Amazing prof.
The class was good, she really helps you out a lot. I respect her honesty too, she will tell you if something is hard or not. It was a good class.
I found the assignments and tests were pretty easy. If you attend class and listen well, you should easily get a good grade.

Very easy class. The teacher is great and very clear on what is expected. E-mails a "manuel d'étudiant" at the start of the semester with all the information in it, including the lectures. You will have an assignment in almost every DGD, but they're all straight-forward.  The only homework there is is reading 2 books and doing 2 300 word projects.

This prof knows her stuff. She gives clear instructions and the workload isn't heavy, even though reading is really important. She connects with the students and is interested in the success of all of them. I have her again next semester and I am not a tad worried.

J'ai quand même aimé ce cours. La prof est jeune et cela se voit peut-être dans l'efficacité de son organisation du plan de cours. Mais elle enseigne bien et est passionnée et c'est cela qui compte. Les examens sont assez imprévisibles, et ils ont souvent pris la classe par surprise... Mais j'ai beaucoup appris.
